
                            HEAD
                         /        ^
   git reset -- files   |         |
                         \         git commit
                            STAGE
                         /        ^
  git checkout -- files |         |
                         \         git add files
                         WORKING_DIR

git init
  - create a new git repository
git add
  - propose changes (add this content to the next commit)
git commit -m "Commit message"
  - commit changes
git commit -a
  - stage every file that is already tracked before doing the commit (no need of git add)
git rm
  - remove a file from your staging area and working directory
git log
  - view the commit history
git diff
  - That command compares your working directory to your staging area. The result tells you the changes you’ve made that you haven’t yet staged.
git diff --staged
  - That command compares your staged changes to your last commit
